(35, 1, '2012-01-14 13:42:58', '2012-01-14 13:42:58', 'Affiliate marketing may seem tedious and complex, but if you are smart about it, you can make serious money. However, do not worry. The following tips will help you avoid some of the common pitfalls.\n\nGive careful consideration before linking to products on your site. Arranging the affiliate links you have on your site may take some time, but presentation is an important factor in increasing your profits.\n\nToo many banners make a site appear confusing so try to avoid overusing them. If your site looks to pushy and unprofessional, then people will not want to visit your site. Don''t let the banners on your site contain all the information, your content should be the most informative part.\n\nTo get ahead of your competitors, get a good number of Google Plus fans following you. Integrate Google Plus into your site and into your other social networking circles. Make sure your content provides customers an incentive to follow your site.\n\nYou can tell customers on your site that they can become an affiliate as well. When they purchase your product, ask them if they would like to earn some money by selling it for you. If your customer chooses be your affiliate, that one sale can lead to thousands of sales. This can help you get a big increase in profits and you will have better affiliate marketing as well.\n\nBecause Google and other companies put special focus on social media websites, it is imperative that you do the same. The search engines use the links on social media websites to help determine search rankings. Linking to sites like Twitter and Facebook along with a comment section and tweets will help your site get recognized.\n\nAlways consider your target customers when choosing items for affiliate marketing techniques. You can sell cheap products in large volumes by offering low-click-through options. More expensive products call for more intense, focused selling, to raise the ratio of customers versus visitors.\n\nYou should always be honest when participating in affiliate marketing, and you will find that the people who visit your site will be affected in a positive way. When you are doing affiliate marketing, remember that honesty is important. If your readers see that you are marketing your products in good faith, they are far more likely to respond positively and buy your products.\n\nAs you are now aware, affiliate marketing is simpler than it first appears. Though it requires study and hard work, plus reaching out to a network, the benefits to your business will make it worthwhile. Keep these ideas in mind in order to have more affiliate marketing success.', 'Try These Tips If You Want To Succeed In Affiliate Marketing', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '33-revision', '', '', '2012-01-14 13:42:58', '2012-01-14 13:42:58', '', 33, 'http://yourwebsitedomain.com/33-revision/35/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(36, 1, '2012-01-14 20:43:32', '2012-01-14 20:43:32', '<a href="http://yourwebsitedomain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Affiliate-Marketing5.jpg"><img src="http://yourwebsitedomain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/Affiliate-Marketing5.jpg" alt="" title="volunteer" width="439" height="273" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-37" /></a>If you are a stranger to the universe that is affiliate marketing, a few pointers and helpful hints will prove immensely beneficial to your start. Continue reading for some great tips to help get you on your way with your new affiliate marketing plan.\r\n\r\nAll good affiliate marketers know that pay-per-sale marketing plans are extremely risky. However, for people who can make it work, it''s a lucrative method. Before deciding to go with this type of marketing plan, you should take time to see if this particular affiliate is good for your website.\r\n\r\nDon''t underestimate the power of a link''s visual location on your website. Test your link on different parts of the page and compare the results. Use the same content; the only thing to change is the placement of the link.\r\n\r\nAffiliate promoters should embrace new selling methods, such as text-message campaigns. While the technique is somewhat novel, many affiliate partners have discovered text services to be a great way to communicate with consumers and generate awareness about their newest offerings.\r\n\r\nUse your advertising budget carefully in order to bring in the most revenue. By purchasing targeted keyword ads, it will drive more visitors to your site. Increased site traffic means that you have more potential customers seeing your products.\r\n\r\nIf the company is constantly putting out new products you should try them out! If a company is always putting new products on the market, this is the one you want to go with. Avoid one-trick ponies and fads.\r\n\r\nA tracking service can be a very useful tool. If an affiliate doesn''t calculate your sales correctly, the tracking service can prove that the total isn''t correct. This can be avoided from the beginning if you make sure to use a reputable tracking service. An independent service you pay for will pay for itself by preventing the loss of commissions.\r\n\r\nKnowing your audience will make you successful through affiliate marketing. You should strive to provide your readers with the things they want. By analyzing what your visitors are looking for, you can better provide it. What is it that they find valuable about your site?\r\n\r\nAffiliate marketing sometimes requires start-up investment. Continue to reinvestment money into affiliate marketing ventures to gain further growth. Facebook is such a large social networking arena that it is a wonderful site to advertise on if you do so correctly. Google, Yahoo and MySpace are other such sites.\r\n\r\nAs the article above shows, affiliate marketing can help drive exposure of the products and services your site offers. By following these ideas, you now have a greater understanding about affiliate marketing.', 'Beginners Guide To Affiliate Marketing To Help You Get Started', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beginners-guide-to-affiliate-marketing-to-help-you-get-started', '', '', '2012-01-14 13:44:47', '2012-01-14 13:44:47', '', 0, 'http://yourwebsitedomain.com/?p=36', 0, 'post', '', 0),
