(45, 1, '2012-01-16 13:47:36', '2012-01-16 13:47:36', '<a href="http://yourwebsitedomain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/affiliate-marketing8.jpg"><img src="http://yourwebsitedomain.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/affiliate-marketing8.jpg" alt="" title="percent symbol" width="400" height="300" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-46" /></a>Affiliate marketing can be an extremely lucrative marketing opportunity. It has long been used by knowledgeable webmasters to increase their profits. Due to the fact that it has been around for so long, and the fact that it is constantly evolving, there is a wealth of information on affiliate marketing that you can take advantage of. Beginners and experts alike always benefit from new tips on affiliate marketing every now and again.\r\n\r\nAlways promote products that you believe in. The products you promote are a reflection of your website and yourself. The quality of the products and services you promote will determine how much trust your potential customers place in you and your business. You can keep customers if you promote good products and prices.\r\n\r\nOne easy way to assess affiliate programs is to compare their conversion rates. Use a one percent conversion ratio.\r\n\r\nWhen putting in affiliate links, think of all the accessory items you can include in your website. Consider a strapped water bottle so they will have the option to bring it out.\r\n\r\nMany affiliate marketers cannot resist the temptation to push the process to the limits. They try to push too many products and promotions rather than concentrating on their core products which is a necessity in the cutthroat world of affiliate marketing. Remember, maximum results aren''t attainable all at once. Once you find the approach that works for you, you can make a lot of money in affiliate marketing.\r\n\r\nOnce you have generated a good amount of sales as an affiliate promoter, consider asking for a higher commission percentage from the affiliate program you belong to. If you are generating enough sales, the marketing program you joined will be eager to keep you.\r\n\r\nIt is better to start small when you are first establishing your affiliate marketing program. This gives you a better shot at success, and you will learn as you progress. Then when you branch out to more competitive niches, you will have more knowledge.\r\n\r\nSo called "secret links" can be a subtle, yet effective strategy. There are certain ways you can embed affiliate links throughout your articles and other content without being obnoxious or blatant about it. You should use these tips, but let your readers know about it. Inform your site visitors what will happen if they click on a link.\r\n\r\nThere is no shortage of money to earn from affiliate marketing. But, as with any new venture, doing your research will pay off in terms of your success.', 'Learn To Conduct Affiliate Marketing With These Suggestions ', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'learn-to-conduct-affiliate-marketing-with-these-suggestions', '', '', '2012-01-14 13:49:01', '2012-01-14 13:49:01', '', 0, 'http://yourwebsitedomain.com/?p=45', 0, 'post', '', 0),
